The paper deals with a data structure problem related to range queries, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and data structures. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of probability and randomness in the data structure, which suggests a connection to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper proposes lower bounds on the query time, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
